Description: Rim and wall sherd (mended from seven sherds and plaster) of North Ionian black-figured pottery dinos; orange clay with white inclusions; interior: reserved save inside of rim; on top of rim stopt maeander; exterior, cream slip; tongues, every fourth red at top of shoulder; band with added red band lined in white below; animal frieze sporadically preserved; at left sphinxes (wearing poloi) with raised paws to either side of goose to left; further right probably two bulls in an antithetical composition; inscription cut on exterior.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GG.402)
